summary: That Hades/Persephone Frostiron AU no one asked for
body:
That Hades/Persephone Frostiron AU no one asked for

“I’ve never wanted to be the God of Spring”, Tony spats at Loki, who doesn’t even turn around to look at him. “Fuck, I don’t even like spring! I can’t stand everyone making such a big deal out of things blooming as if that doesn’t happen every year. I hate being woken up by birds at five am. Pollen is ruining my life. I’ve never had a green thumb; I suck at gardening. I don’t care about flowers. So if you think I’ll walk around here and make an enchanted garden out of your goddamn lair full of zombies, prepare for the biggest disappointment of your life.”

Loki still doesn’t turn around, and Tony stands there and stares and breathes raggedly until Loki says, “but you are the God of Spring.”

“Well, fuck that. I don’t want to be it.”

Loki inclines his head so Tony can see the older god’s profile. The bastard is smirking. “And I do not want to be the God of Death. I don’t see how that changes anything.”

And with that, Loki leaves him alone.

________________________________

Later, much later, Tony’s staring at Loki again. He’s not breathing raggedly this time, though, and he isn’t standing, either. He’s lying, just like Loki - on top of Loki, in fact; at least more or less. Loki’s naked body is warm, only his hands are cold. They always are, and Tony likes it.

“What are you the God of?”, Loki asks as he lazily rakes his fingers through Tony’s hair. That smile Tony likes the most is tugging at his lover’s lips now, and of course he grins back.

“Creation”, he answers, “and you?”

Loki’s dark eyes crinkle with amusement. “Fire.”

And that’s a good combination, as far as Tony is concerned.

summary: Tony’s been presumed dead for a few issues after an attack by the Mandarin, and he rolled with it because he currently can’t...
caption:
Tony’s been presumed dead for a few issues after an attack by the Mandarin, and he rolled with it because he currently can’t survive without wearing his entire suit.  However, he’s now finally found a way to modify his “master transistor” and is making his triumphant return.  His first course of action is apparently to realize that Happy’s in love with Pepper and to remove himself from the picture (romantically) so that she can be with Happy instead.

- Tales of Suspense Vol 1 #63 (1965)

blog.name: tonystarkismyprompt
blog.title: Tony Stark Fanfic Prompts
blog.description:
Basically a bunch of prompts about Tony Stark/the Avengers. 
(please write me some fics)

body:
Tony Stark Prompt:

“Family dinner? What? Why? We’re not even a family.”

“It’s Thanksgiving, Tony, that’s what people do.”

“That doesn’t change the fact that it’s typically a family occasion.”

“After all that we’ve been through, I’d say we’re a family and then some.”

(I just want some happy, familial, domestic Avengers for Thanksgiving.)
